section.docs-section
  markdown:
    ## Anchor Points
    {: #anchor }

    Control the anchor point of your tip.  By defualt, tips are anchored to the center point of the element you are tipping. Add the modifier classes, `.tip--anchor-left` and `.tip--anchor-right`,  to anchor to the left or right. As you might expect, anchor control only works with `.tip--top` and `.tip--bottom`.

  table.table
    tr
      td
        markdown:
          [Hover here](#){: class="has-tip tip--anchor-left" data-tip="I'm anchored on the left." }
      td
        markdown:
          `.has-tip.tip--anchor-left`
      td Anchored Left, Top
    tr
      td
        markdown:
          [Hover here](#){: class="has-tip tip--anchor-right" data-tip="I'm anchored on the right." }
      td
        markdown:
          `.has-tip.tip--anchor-right`
      td Anchored Right, Top
    tr
      td
        markdown:
          [Hover here](#){: class="has-tip tip--bottom tip--anchor-left" data-tip="I'm anchored on the bottom-left." }
      td
        markdown:
          `.has-tip.tip--bottom.tip--anchor-left`
      td Anchored Left, Bottom
    tr
      td
        markdown:
          [Hover here](#){: class="has-tip tip--bottom tip--anchor-right" data-tip="I'm anchored on the bottom-right." }
      td
        markdown:
